let is declared globally and acessed globally
var is declared golbally and can be acessed with in the scope 
{    } -> the code between this braces is called scope
const is block scoped variable which can not be changed

The defer attribute in a <script> tag is a powerful tool for optimizing webpage loading,
When a browser encounters a <script> tag with the defer attribute,
it begins downloading the script in the background while continuing to parse the HTML

an expression is a piece of code that produces a value ( x + 10)

let a = 5;
console.log(a++);
console.log(++a);
